

 Library Management System (Frontend Prototype)

 Project Overview

The Library Management System is a frontend-based web application that simulates basic library operations. It provides separate interfaces for Admin and User roles, enabling management of books, memberships, and transactions.

The project is developed using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Browser localStorage is used to simulate data storage.


 Objectives

* To implement a basic library workflow
* To provide role-based access (Admin and User)
* To implement validations on forms
* To simulate dynamic behavior without backend



 Modules

 Admin Module

Admin has access to:

* Maintenance

  * Add Membership
  * Update Membership
  * Add Book/Movie
  * Update Book/Movie
  * User Management

* Transactions

  * Check Book Availability
  * Issue Book
  * Return Book

* Reports

  * Master List of Books
  * Master List of Movies
  * Master List of Memberships
  * Active Issues
  * Overdue Returns
  * Issue Requests

User Module

User has access to:

* Search books
* View issued books
* View return date and status
* Return books

User cannot:

* Access maintenance
* Issue books directly



 Login System

The system uses a simple role-based login:

* If username is "admin" → Admin Dashboard
* Any other input → User Dashboard

Passwords are hidden using password input fields.

 Workflow

 Admin Flow

Admin Login → Dashboard → Transactions → Issue Book → Success

User Flow

User Login → Dashboard → Search Book → View Results → Return Book → Fine Payment (if applicable)



 Features Implemented

* Role-based access control
* Form validations
* Issue date cannot be earlier than current date
* Return date automatically set to 15 days from issue date
* Fine validation using checkbox
* Use of radio buttons and checkboxes as required
* Data storage using localStorage



 Technologies Used

* HTML
* CSS
* JavaScript
* localStorage


 Project Structure

Library-Management-System/
│
